    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Put a large baking tray (or two) in the oven to heat up (this will stop the pizza bottom[s] from going soggy)</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-shallot-pizza-with-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>sausage meat</strong> (remove the paper if required!)<strong> </strong>to the pan and breaking it up into bite-sized pieces with a wooden spoon and cook for 5-7 min or until crispy and nearly cooked through</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-shallot-pizza-with-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Add 5 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[7 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [10 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-shallot-pizza-with-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-shallot-pizza-with-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the heated tray[s] from the oven and add your<strong> pizza base[s]</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>tomato sauce </strong>between the<strong> pizza base[s]</strong> and spread it evenly all over with the back of a spoon</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-shallot-pizza-with-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the pizza[s] with the <strong>torn mozzarella</strong>,<strong> sausage</strong> <strong>meat</strong> and <strong>sliced shallot</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over your <strong>dried oregano</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min or until the sausage is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the base[s] is crisp \u2013 this your <strong>sausage & shallot pizza[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-shallot-pizza-with-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and <strong>Dijon mustard </strong>(not a mustard fan? Go easy!) in a bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-shallot-pizza-with-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sausage & shallot pizzas</strong> with the <strong>salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the<strong> dressing</strong> over the salad</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
